Week #1 Results:

Week #1 proved to be a tough bite for most teams with post cold front conditions.  Eric and Adam Spray took top honors weighing in 2 fish for 6 lbs 10 oz and also had the big fish of the night, a 4 lb 1 oz walleye.  In second place was Rick and Brennen Longnecker, who weighed 3 fish for 5 lbs 8 oz.  Pete McGinty and Dave Fernholz (subbing for Dallas Croatt), weighed in 1 fish for 2 lbs 14 oz to take third place.

Week #2 Results:

Week #2 was another tough bite.  Teams were faced again with post cold front conditions and very dirty water conditions.  Only 3 fish were brought to the scale.  There was a tie for first place between Corey/Jerry Heinrich and Rick/Brennen Longnecker.  Heinrichs weighed 1 fish for 9 lbs 14 oz and Longneckers weighed 2 fish for 9 lbs 14 oz.  Corey and Jerry Heinrich took big fish honors for the night.

